WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.035 --> 00:00:05.671
[machinery rattling.
background chatter]

2
00:00:05.673 --> 00:00:09.508
- We are on the verge
of taking that mountain.

3
00:00:09.510 --> 00:00:12.544
Thanks to you
and your steam shovel.

4
00:00:12.546 --> 00:00:15.647
You can't quit now.
I-I-I-I won't allow it!

5
00:00:15.649 --> 00:00:17.883
- Railroad's your dream.

6
00:00:22.856 --> 00:00:25.724
- Cullen...

7
00:00:25.726 --> 00:00:28.293
What happened to ruth?

8
00:00:28.295 --> 00:00:31.563
You gave her every chance
to walk away from her deed.

9
00:00:31.565 --> 00:00:35.868
- No. it ain't about
what I gave her.

10
00:00:35.870 --> 00:00:39.405
- She threw her life away
on an empty ideal.

11
00:00:39.407 --> 00:00:43.142
Is that what you want?

12
00:00:46.312 --> 00:00:48.680
- I'm going home. doc.

13
00:00:48.682 --> 00:00:51.383
- Home?

14
00:00:57.657 --> 00:01:00.025
This is your home.

15
00:01:03.596 --> 00:01:06.665
- [sighs]
listen to me.

16
00:01:06.667 --> 00:01:09.668
In the not too distant future.
this railroad will be finished.

17
00:01:09.670 --> 00:01:10.936
I will be back in new york.

18
00:01:10.938 --> 00:01:14.873
And I will need someone
I can trust out here.

19
00:01:14.875 --> 00:01:16.442
- You got delaney.
He's a good engineer.

20
00:01:16.444 --> 00:01:17.743
- Delaney.

21
00:01:17.745 --> 00:01:19.545
Delaney is not half the man
you are.

22
00:01:19.547 --> 00:01:21.547
- Might be more if you
treat him right.

23
00:01:21.549 --> 00:01:23.749
- I don't think you understand
what I've done for you.

24
00:01:23.751 --> 00:01:26.952
What--what I'm offering you.

25
00:01:26.954 --> 00:01:30.355
What your family needs from you.

26
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:38.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

27
00:01:44.537 --> 00:01:47.206
[sighs]

28
00:02:05.658 --> 00:02:09.061
I won't take you back.

29
00:02:09.063 --> 00:02:11.897
Not again.

30
00:02:20.673 --> 00:02:22.541
- Yeah. I know it.

31
00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:31.183
[distant voices]

32
00:02:31.185 --> 00:02:35.754
[machinery rumbling]

33
00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:50.536
- I asked mr. Delaney make sure
that boiler don't run dry.

34
00:02:50.538 --> 00:02:53.372
It do. we'll be pickin' iron
out our ass 'til christmas.

35
00:02:53.374 --> 00:02:54.606
[chuckles]

36
00:02:56.709 --> 00:02:58.277
- You make sure you get to

37
00:02:58.279 --> 00:03:01.046
The top of that mountain.
psalms.

38
00:03:01.048 --> 00:03:03.649
- You make sure you make it
to where you goin' too.

39
00:03:03.651 --> 00:03:05.584
Mr. Bohannon.

40
00:03:27.473 --> 00:03:31.610
[grunting]

41
00:03:46.359 --> 00:03:48.594
- Yep.

42
00:03:49.662 --> 00:03:50.762
[clicks tongue]

43
00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:09.081
[western folk music]

44
00:04:09.083 --> 00:04:17.155
â™ª

45
00:04:50.723 --> 00:04:53.158
- Hello?

46
00:04:55.328 --> 00:04:57.562
Anyone here?

47
00:05:03.803 --> 00:05:07.272
Father hatch?

48
00:05:07.274 --> 00:05:08.840
Whoa.

49
00:05:39.205 --> 00:05:41.573
[animal grunts]

50
00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:46.678
[snuffling. growling]

51
00:05:48.548 --> 00:05:50.649
- Go! Get outta here!

52
00:05:50.651 --> 00:05:52.184
Skit!

53
00:05:52.186 --> 00:05:53.518
Go!

54
00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:56.722
[animal growling]

55
00:06:07.567 --> 00:06:10.769
[crows cawing]

56
00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:03.855
Elder moss.

57
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.031
Wh-what happened?

58
00:07:13.033 --> 00:07:16.635
Huh? Where is everybody?

59
00:07:16.637 --> 00:07:19.938
Where is everybody?
Where is everybody?

60
00:07:21.574 --> 00:07:25.110
- [hoarsely]
na-o-mi...

61
00:07:25.112 --> 00:07:26.578
- Naomi. yeah.

62
00:07:26.580 --> 00:07:28.046
Yeah. where is she?
Where's naomi?

63
00:07:28.048 --> 00:07:29.214
Huh? Where's naomi?

64
00:07:29.216 --> 00:07:32.217
- [gasping]

65
00:07:32.219 --> 00:07:35.620
[long exhale]

66
00:07:35.622 --> 00:07:36.955
- Elder moss?

67
00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:39.658
Elder moss?

68
00:07:41.594 --> 00:07:45.630
Elder moss!

69
00:08:40.052 --> 00:08:43.588
- It appears you've ruffled
feathers. miss ellison.

70
00:08:47.193 --> 00:08:50.762
- I will not be intimidated.
mr. Campbell.

71
00:08:54.233 --> 00:08:55.867
Get out.

72
00:08:55.869 --> 00:08:59.671
- I didn't come here to rehash.
louise.

73
00:08:59.673 --> 00:09:01.873
I came here to talk
about the future.

74
00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.575
Our future.

75
00:09:03.577 --> 00:09:06.578
I intend to purchase
<i>the leader</i> from durant.

76
00:09:06.580 --> 00:09:10.749
But only if you agree to stay.

77
00:09:10.751 --> 00:09:13.718
- And this is my sugar?

78
00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:16.521
- Territory status is upon us.

79
00:09:16.523 --> 00:09:19.024
A territory needs a press.

80
00:09:19.026 --> 00:09:20.692
Voice of progress.

81
00:09:20.694 --> 00:09:23.562
A national voice.

82
00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:27.399
I plan to give it to you.

83
00:09:27.401 --> 00:09:30.535
Along with my full protection.

84
00:09:30.537 --> 00:09:35.874
We'll rebuild this newspaper
together.

85
00:09:35.876 --> 00:09:38.209
- How incredibly generous.

86
00:09:38.211 --> 00:09:40.745
- You accept my offer. then?

87
00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:43.915
- No.
I reject it absolutely.

88
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:46.551
But I would like to thank you.

89
00:09:46.553 --> 00:09:49.554
For days. I've been feeling
useless. futile.

90
00:09:49.556 --> 00:09:52.524
I was losing the sense that
my profession even mattered.

91
00:09:52.526 --> 00:09:56.595
That my...Newspaper mattered.

92
00:09:56.597 --> 00:10:00.432
But obviously. it does.

93
00:10:00.434 --> 00:10:03.835
I will never let you
take it from me.

94
00:10:08.641 --> 00:10:09.975
[chicken squawks]

95
00:11:27.653 --> 00:11:30.689
[background chatter]

96
00:11:45.237 --> 00:11:48.640
[overlapping chatter.
laughter]

97
00:11:57.983 --> 00:12:02.253
- Need a room and a bath.
A barber if you got one.

98
00:12:02.255 --> 00:12:05.156
- If you'll sign in.

99
00:12:05.158 --> 00:12:08.593
- Yeah.

100
00:12:08.595 --> 00:12:11.229
- Cullen bohannon.

101
00:12:11.231 --> 00:12:15.934
I thought that ragged
countenance bore a resemblance.

102
00:12:15.936 --> 00:12:18.703
You. sir. have come a long way
for nothing.

103
00:12:18.705 --> 00:12:20.505
- Yeah?
How's that?

104
00:12:20.507 --> 00:12:22.707
- Pestilential grasshopper
has brought plague

105
00:12:22.709 --> 00:12:24.375
To this city that has left

106
00:12:24.377 --> 00:12:28.680
A lack of circulating currency
and a surplus of laborers.

107
00:12:28.682 --> 00:12:32.751
I have made a deal
with brigham young for 800 men.

108
00:12:32.753 --> 00:12:37.956
Haven't left a hirable worker
within 500 miles.

109
00:12:37.958 --> 00:12:40.291
- You stable yourselves?
- Yes. sir.

110
00:12:40.293 --> 00:12:42.727
- I got one horse.

111
00:12:42.729 --> 00:12:46.631
- My spies tell me that durant
is cresting sherman peak.

112
00:12:46.633 --> 00:12:49.100
- He is.

113
00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:52.871
- And that his new steam engine
shovel was your invention.

114
00:12:52.873 --> 00:12:54.239
- It was.

115
00:12:54.241 --> 00:12:56.074
- They tell me something
else. too.

116
00:12:56.076 --> 00:12:58.576
That you quit the u.P.

117
00:12:58.578 --> 00:13:02.447
Is that true?

118
00:13:06.752 --> 00:13:08.419
Well. I am curious.

119
00:13:08.421 --> 00:13:10.955
What brings you to this mecca
of polygamist pretension?

120
00:13:10.957 --> 00:13:13.758
- Searching for my wife
and my boy.

121
00:13:13.760 --> 00:13:15.660
Think they might be here.

122
00:13:15.662 --> 00:13:17.562
She's mormon.

123
00:13:17.564 --> 00:13:19.330
Excuse me.

124
00:13:19.332 --> 00:13:22.467
- Mr. Bohannon.

125
00:13:22.469 --> 00:13:26.237
Brigham young is rumored
to have a bed 7 feet long

126
00:13:26.239 --> 00:13:30.275
By 96 feet wide
to accommodate his 55 wives.

127
00:13:30.277 --> 00:13:33.344
I do hope yours
is not found among 'em.

128
00:13:38.517 --> 00:13:39.818
- You know what the wagons cost.

129
00:13:39.820 --> 00:13:42.420
My brother broke it
down to the red cent.

130
00:13:42.422 --> 00:13:43.588
He does the figuring.

131
00:13:43.590 --> 00:13:45.190
It's a fair price.

132
00:13:50.029 --> 00:13:53.731
- The figures don't tell all.
mr. Spinoza.

133
00:13:56.535 --> 00:13:58.269
- When you get your damn fill
of starin'.

134
00:13:58.271 --> 00:13:59.771
Let us know if we got a deal.

135
00:13:59.773 --> 00:14:03.541
- You are speaking
with god's high minister.

136
00:14:03.543 --> 00:14:06.511
Profanity will not do.

137
00:14:06.513 --> 00:14:08.713
- Brother gundersen.

138
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:21.292
- 'course. uh.
you used your own horses.

139
00:14:21.294 --> 00:14:22.660
That's a savings.

140
00:14:22.662 --> 00:14:27.532
- Do not negotiate with the man.
zeke.

141
00:14:27.534 --> 00:14:31.636
He's god's whatsit.

142
00:14:31.638 --> 00:14:34.572
Just like last time. mr. Young.

143
00:14:34.574 --> 00:14:36.674
The numbers is what they are.

144
00:14:36.676 --> 00:14:42.080
- And what they are is too high.
my benighted friend.

145
00:14:42.082 --> 00:14:43.715
Lower your price

146
00:14:43.717 --> 00:14:46.718
If you wish to transport
our mormon workmen west.

147
00:14:46.720 --> 00:14:49.420
- What I wish for
is for fair profit.

148
00:14:53.759 --> 00:14:56.628
- I have consulted and prayed...

149
00:15:00.432 --> 00:15:03.835
And here is what I will pay.

150
00:15:18.550 --> 00:15:21.953
- You can get your damn wagons
somewhere else.

151
00:15:26.892 --> 00:15:29.594
Zeke.

152
00:15:32.965 --> 00:15:34.265
- [murmurs]

153
00:15:36.535 --> 00:15:38.603
- Leave the door open.
brother gundersen.

154
00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:41.372
- To release
the polluting vapors.

155
00:15:41.374 --> 00:15:42.707
- [chuckles]

156
00:15:42.709 --> 00:15:44.909
I take it the price
would have been lower

157
00:15:44.911 --> 00:15:46.577
Had we not been mormons.

158
00:15:46.579 --> 00:15:49.647
- Mm.
- Hmm.

159
00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:56.754
- Michael.

160
00:15:56.756 --> 00:15:59.290
Mick.

161
00:15:59.292 --> 00:16:00.892
Ha.

162
00:16:00.894 --> 00:16:03.628
The bleedin' cavalry's comin'.

163
00:16:05.664 --> 00:16:09.600
- What's he want. then?
- Ah. no matter.

164
00:16:09.602 --> 00:16:12.103
I've taken on twice these

165
00:16:12.105 --> 00:16:15.573
With nothin'
but a barstool and water back.

166
00:16:15.575 --> 00:16:17.675
- Mr. Mayor.

167
00:16:19.945 --> 00:16:22.513
From president-elect grant.

168
00:16:22.515 --> 00:16:24.882
Received within the hour.

169
00:16:27.686 --> 00:16:30.955
Acknowledging the basic judicial
system I have established here.

170
00:16:30.957 --> 00:16:34.959
Authorizing the creation
of a legislature

171
00:16:34.961 --> 00:16:39.731
And the removal of
the "provisional" from my title.

172
00:16:42.501 --> 00:16:43.768
- Fancy words.

173
00:16:43.770 --> 00:16:45.870
- You and your men
will leave cheyenne.

174
00:16:45.872 --> 00:16:47.505
- And what if we don't have
a mind to?

175
00:16:47.507 --> 00:16:50.508
- You'll be taken
into custody and shot.

176
00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:52.677
- On what charges and by whom?

177
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:55.213
- Conspiracy and attempted
assassination

178
00:16:55.215 --> 00:16:56.280
Of a government official...

179
00:16:56.282 --> 00:16:58.282
- [belches]

180
00:16:58.284 --> 00:16:59.617
- And by me.

181
00:16:59.619 --> 00:17:01.719
- Like hell.
- [indistinct order]

182
00:17:09.328 --> 00:17:11.162
- Good news.

183
00:17:11.164 --> 00:17:15.700
There's a train leaving
tomorrow morning.

184
00:17:15.702 --> 00:17:19.437
You'd best be on it.

185
00:17:27.246 --> 00:17:28.980
- This here's a credit ledger
for the fort.

186
00:17:28.982 --> 00:17:31.182
It's got written down the names
of every family member

187
00:17:31.184 --> 00:17:32.750
Who lived there.

188
00:17:32.752 --> 00:17:34.685
Any survivors
in it would have come here.

189
00:17:34.687 --> 00:17:36.854
- You don't know that.
- They need brigham young's

190
00:17:36.856 --> 00:17:39.557
Permission to settle elsewheres.
and we both know that.

191
00:17:39.559 --> 00:17:42.627
- I can't help you. gentile.

192
00:17:44.530 --> 00:17:45.930
- Excuse me.

193
00:17:45.932 --> 00:17:47.432
You'd have a record
of where they went.

194
00:17:47.434 --> 00:17:48.533
And that's all I'm asking for.

195
00:17:48.535 --> 00:17:50.735
- Sir. you're not allowed
in here.

196
00:17:50.737 --> 00:17:52.837
- Shit. son.
I ain't allowed anywheres.

197
00:17:52.839 --> 00:17:54.705
- Church records are
a sacred trust and obligation

198
00:17:54.707 --> 00:17:56.741
Brought forth by joseph smith
himself.

199
00:17:56.743 --> 00:17:59.677
Kept by the church
for its members.

200
00:17:59.679 --> 00:18:02.814
- Well. I am a mormon.

201
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:05.183
Was.

202
00:18:08.353 --> 00:18:10.621
My wife is.

203
00:18:10.623 --> 00:18:13.024
Please.

204
00:18:25.537 --> 00:18:28.573
- Fort smith.
wyoming territory?

205
00:18:28.575 --> 00:18:31.209
- Yes. sir.

206
00:18:31.211 --> 00:18:32.543
What--

207
00:18:32.545 --> 00:18:34.212
No. hey!
Ow!

208
00:18:34.214 --> 00:18:36.380
- It wasn't an indian attack
that killed them.

209
00:18:36.382 --> 00:18:39.750
Fort smith was hit by smallpox.

210
00:18:39.752 --> 00:18:41.419
- Small--smallpox?

211
00:18:41.421 --> 00:18:43.221
- The survivors
arrived two weeks ago.

212
00:18:43.223 --> 00:18:45.756
Most of them are sick and dying.

213
00:18:45.758 --> 00:18:46.591
They've been quarantined.

214
00:18:46.593 --> 00:18:49.760
- How--how many survivors?

215
00:18:49.762 --> 00:18:52.196
- Not many.

216
00:19:16.688 --> 00:19:18.856
- Oh. uh...
Looking for my family.

217
00:19:18.858 --> 00:19:22.793
My. uh. wife and boy.
They were at fort smith.

218
00:19:22.795 --> 00:19:24.595
Name's bohannon.

219
00:19:33.639 --> 00:19:36.107
- I'm not seeing anyone
with that name.

220
00:19:36.109 --> 00:19:39.277
- Naomi and william?

221
00:19:39.279 --> 00:19:42.213
Uh...Hatch?

222
00:19:42.215 --> 00:19:44.382
Might be under.

223
00:19:47.686 --> 00:19:49.787
- Oh. yes.
Here it is.

224
00:19:54.459 --> 00:19:57.728
Mist--mr. Bohannon!

225
00:19:57.730 --> 00:19:59.730
Mr. Bohannon. please.

226
00:20:04.703 --> 00:20:06.137
There.

227
00:20:06.139 --> 00:20:08.472
Last bed.

228
00:20:10.075 --> 00:20:13.244
I thought she'd be gone
by now...

229
00:20:13.246 --> 00:20:16.981
But perhaps
she was waiting for you?

230
00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:29.927
- [sniffling]

231
00:20:39.838 --> 00:20:43.040
- H-hold still.

232
00:20:43.042 --> 00:20:44.742
I know it hurts.

233
00:20:44.744 --> 00:20:47.111
[woman sniffles]

234
00:20:47.113 --> 00:20:49.447
- Been three girls
hurt this month.

235
00:20:49.449 --> 00:20:51.616
Cut. noses broke up.

236
00:20:51.618 --> 00:20:53.084
- Same man?

237
00:20:53.086 --> 00:20:56.554
- No.
Whole bunch of 'em.

238
00:20:56.556 --> 00:20:59.190
Dead rabbits. they go by.

239
00:21:01.627 --> 00:21:05.796
- Fix these bandages
in the morning.

240
00:21:05.798 --> 00:21:08.766
- Will I still be pretty
when this heals up?

241
00:21:12.571 --> 00:21:15.172
- Shouldn't be bad.
you care for it.

242
00:21:17.709 --> 00:21:20.711
Your girls are getting hurt
and cut up by customers.

243
00:21:20.713 --> 00:21:22.480
- What business
is that of yours?

244
00:21:22.482 --> 00:21:25.316
- Well. the girls
come to me. is all.

245
00:21:25.318 --> 00:21:28.319
They ain't being looked after.
- I'm leaving cheyenne.

246
00:21:28.321 --> 00:21:30.154
I'm taking 'em with me.

247
00:21:30.156 --> 00:21:33.424
So you won't have to
worry about it.

248
00:21:33.426 --> 00:21:35.626
- Taking 'em where?
- West.

249
00:21:35.628 --> 00:21:37.561
- Cheyenne's been
hard on everyone.

250
00:21:37.563 --> 00:21:39.430
Don't mean you run.

251
00:21:39.432 --> 00:21:41.732
- [laughs]

252
00:21:41.734 --> 00:21:44.302
Campbell gave me a choice.

253
00:21:44.304 --> 00:21:46.504
I chose me life.

254
00:21:46.506 --> 00:21:50.241
- Fine.
I'll come with you.

255
00:21:52.177 --> 00:21:54.278
- You don't even know
where we're going.

256
00:21:54.280 --> 00:21:56.614
- Them girls need caring for.
mickey.

257
00:21:56.616 --> 00:21:59.483
I-I'll see to 'em.
tend to 'em.

258
00:21:59.485 --> 00:22:01.519
And keep 'em in line.

259
00:22:01.521 --> 00:22:04.822
- Make you madam. you mean?

260
00:22:04.824 --> 00:22:06.824
- Partner.

261
00:22:06.826 --> 00:22:09.427
- You need money
to buy into a partnership.

262
00:22:09.429 --> 00:22:11.262
- I got money.

263
00:22:11.264 --> 00:22:15.299
I reckon this'll buy me 15%.

264
00:22:15.301 --> 00:22:17.501
But you say what's right.

265
00:22:21.640 --> 00:22:24.709
Assuming it's money
I need to partner with ya.

266
00:22:27.813 --> 00:22:30.815
- [grunting]

267
00:22:30.817 --> 00:22:32.616
[muttering]
peek-a-boo. hot dang--

268
00:22:32.618 --> 00:22:34.618
Oh. there you go.

269
00:22:34.620 --> 00:22:36.787
[laughs]

270
00:22:36.789 --> 00:22:38.689
[glass clattering]

271
00:22:45.297 --> 00:22:47.365
Oh. yeah.

272
00:22:52.704 --> 00:22:54.638
What do you want.
carrot snapper?

273
00:22:54.640 --> 00:22:55.639
- Ah.

274
00:22:55.641 --> 00:22:57.274
- Uhh...
[thud]

275
00:22:59.244 --> 00:23:02.146
Huh?
[speaking norwegian]

276
00:23:02.148 --> 00:23:03.247
- [moaning]

277
00:23:03.249 --> 00:23:06.884
Huh?
[speaking norwegian]

278
00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:10.755
- [gagging]

279
00:23:10.757 --> 00:23:14.258
- [speaking norwegian]
that's it.

280
00:23:14.260 --> 00:23:18.763
[continues in norwegian]

281
00:23:21.867 --> 00:23:24.235
Shh.

282
00:23:24.237 --> 00:23:25.736
[laughs]

283
00:23:25.738 --> 00:23:29.573
- You find the good stuff.
harry?

284
00:23:29.575 --> 00:23:31.776
- He did.

285
00:23:33.545 --> 00:23:38.749
Oh.
A bottle missing...

286
00:23:38.751 --> 00:23:41.185
- Where's harry?
- You will read here.

287
00:23:41.187 --> 00:23:45.823
The arrangement as much
as brother brigham proposed.

288
00:23:53.965 --> 00:23:56.634
- Impossible...

289
00:23:56.636 --> 00:23:59.303
- You are pleased. brother?

290
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:06.977
- Have the money released.

291
00:24:06.979 --> 00:24:09.647
- Good.

292
00:24:09.649 --> 00:24:12.750
Because. if I may...

293
00:24:12.752 --> 00:24:15.619
- Go ahead.

294
00:24:15.621 --> 00:24:20.057
- I am most happy
to have been able.

295
00:24:20.059 --> 00:24:21.926
In my small way.

296
00:24:21.928 --> 00:24:24.662
To forward
heavenly father's work.

297
00:24:24.664 --> 00:24:28.632
And it is my hope--

298
00:24:28.634 --> 00:24:31.769
I am bold. now. I know--

299
00:24:31.771 --> 00:24:35.673
You can see
what I have done here.

300
00:24:35.675 --> 00:24:39.743
The impossible. you have said.
- Mm.

301
00:24:39.745 --> 00:24:41.612
- You realize what I
could accomplish there.

302
00:24:41.614 --> 00:24:45.416
Among our workers
on the central pacific?

303
00:24:48.620 --> 00:24:50.321
- You wish to join huntington?

304
00:24:50.323 --> 00:24:52.256
Is that it?

305
00:24:52.258 --> 00:24:55.359
I have answered you once.

306
00:24:55.361 --> 00:25:00.664
- I join no one.

307
00:25:00.666 --> 00:25:04.668
I am your servant.

308
00:25:04.670 --> 00:25:06.770
And the lord's.

309
00:25:06.772 --> 00:25:09.273
Never huntington's.

310
00:25:09.275 --> 00:25:11.442
There as here.

311
00:25:11.444 --> 00:25:13.677
I look after our interest

312
00:25:13.679 --> 00:25:19.383
And the souls
of our mormon brethren.

313
00:25:19.385 --> 00:25:21.519
You see now

314
00:25:21.521 --> 00:25:26.123
How I might be effective?

315
00:25:45.911 --> 00:25:48.679
- You...

316
00:25:48.681 --> 00:25:50.748
- Yeah.

317
00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:53.017
I come for naomi...

318
00:25:53.019 --> 00:25:56.020
And william.

319
00:25:56.022 --> 00:25:58.722
Are they alive?

320
00:26:03.495 --> 00:26:05.563
[sniffles]

321
00:26:05.565 --> 00:26:08.532
Where are they?

322
00:26:08.534 --> 00:26:13.704
- [whispers] I prayed...
He'd take me...

323
00:26:13.706 --> 00:26:16.674
Not them.

324
00:26:16.676 --> 00:26:20.010
I prayed...

325
00:26:20.012 --> 00:26:22.613
- Where are they. mother hatch?

326
00:26:25.717 --> 00:26:27.952
- West...

327
00:26:27.954 --> 00:26:32.756
Where you'll never find them.

328
00:26:32.758 --> 00:26:35.492
Away from you.

329
00:26:46.638 --> 00:26:49.273
- I'll stay with you.
mother hatch.

330
00:26:49.275 --> 00:26:51.342
[coughing in background]

331
00:26:55.146 --> 00:26:59.750
I'll watch you die.

332
00:26:59.752 --> 00:27:02.686
I'll make sure
they burn you good.

333
00:27:06.291 --> 00:27:09.593
When I find naomi.

334
00:27:09.595 --> 00:27:15.232
I'll tell her
you were miserable to the end.

335
00:27:15.234 --> 00:27:20.337
When my son grows old enough
to know his grandparents...

336
00:27:23.508 --> 00:27:27.745
I will make sure
he never hears your name.

337
00:27:33.184 --> 00:27:39.256
- [coughing]

338
00:27:40.959 --> 00:27:43.427
[gasps. liquid gurgles]

339
00:27:57.609 --> 00:28:01.679
- Mr. Bohannon?

340
00:28:03.281 --> 00:28:04.748
Mr. Bohannon?

341
00:28:08.486 --> 00:28:10.688
Rest easy. brother bohannon.

342
00:28:10.690 --> 00:28:14.224
She died peaceful.
knowing you were here.

343
00:28:19.831 --> 00:28:23.167
- You listen to me.

344
00:28:23.169 --> 00:28:28.338
She was a vengeful woman.

345
00:28:28.340 --> 00:28:31.308
She died the same.

346
00:28:37.148 --> 00:28:40.651
[background conversation]
[wagons rattling]

347
00:28:54.499 --> 00:28:57.034
- Mr. Bohannon.

348
00:28:57.036 --> 00:29:01.538
Good-bye. sir.
I'm just leaving for california.

349
00:29:01.540 --> 00:29:03.540
Did you find your family?

350
00:29:03.542 --> 00:29:05.843
- Searched high and low.

351
00:29:05.845 --> 00:29:07.444
They ain't here.

352
00:29:07.446 --> 00:29:09.012
- Well. sir.

353
00:29:09.014 --> 00:29:11.682
You have the visage of a man
who could use a drink.

354
00:29:11.684 --> 00:29:13.751
- Searched high and low
for that too.

355
00:29:13.753 --> 00:29:15.686
Ain't here.

356
00:29:15.688 --> 00:29:18.122
- Well. then it is fortuitous
that you have run into me.

357
00:29:18.124 --> 00:29:19.523
[pats wagon]

358
00:29:25.063 --> 00:29:27.197
Come along. sir.

359
00:29:27.199 --> 00:29:29.633
Let us imbibe in our comfort.

360
00:29:37.575 --> 00:29:41.111
- Come in. why don't you?

361
00:29:41.113 --> 00:29:44.148
- The cheyenne palace is mine.

362
00:29:44.150 --> 00:29:46.583
The comfort house is mine.

363
00:29:46.585 --> 00:29:49.253
Jailhouse across the street...

364
00:29:49.255 --> 00:29:50.754
Mine.

365
00:29:50.756 --> 00:29:53.657
The hotel...

366
00:29:53.659 --> 00:29:56.593
Will be mine.
one way or another.

367
00:29:56.595 --> 00:29:59.062
Now. that leaves

368
00:29:59.064 --> 00:30:02.399
Just one outstanding item.

369
00:30:02.401 --> 00:30:04.701
- Which is?

370
00:30:06.771 --> 00:30:09.606
- Chicken hill.

371
00:30:09.608 --> 00:30:12.910
Accept my offer
of fair market value

372
00:30:12.912 --> 00:30:16.446
Or surrender it
to the u.S. Cavalry.

373
00:30:16.448 --> 00:30:19.516
Who will bivouac there until
permanent barracks

374
00:30:19.518 --> 00:30:21.985
Can be constructed.

375
00:30:32.197 --> 00:30:35.799
- [exhales]
you want chicken hill?

376
00:30:35.801 --> 00:30:37.701
Take it.

377
00:30:40.205 --> 00:30:42.539
There's the deed.

378
00:30:42.541 --> 00:30:47.544
Now. if you can take it off
my desk. it's yours.

379
00:30:48.780 --> 00:30:54.518
- [laughing]

380
00:30:54.520 --> 00:30:58.522
[distant clanging.
wagons rattling]

381
00:31:00.992 --> 00:31:02.726
- [grunts]
- aah!

382
00:31:04.495 --> 00:31:07.731
[grunting and groaning]

383
00:31:20.044 --> 00:31:22.012
- [screaming]

384
00:31:22.014 --> 00:31:23.780
- Ow!

385
00:31:41.199 --> 00:31:43.100
- How 'bout that?

386
00:31:43.102 --> 00:31:46.103
[both panting]

387
00:31:57.615 --> 00:31:58.949
[thwack. squish]
- ow!

388
00:32:02.287 --> 00:32:04.421
[women giggling]

389
00:32:16.134 --> 00:32:19.036
[thud]
- oh!

390
00:32:23.207 --> 00:32:24.975
- Uh--
- ah!

391
00:32:24.977 --> 00:32:26.610
[scattered laughter]

392
00:32:37.789 --> 00:32:40.290
[men continue grunting]

393
00:32:40.292 --> 00:32:42.559
- Should we intervene. major?

394
00:32:42.561 --> 00:32:45.228
- Only if guns come out.

395
00:32:54.572 --> 00:32:56.807
[man laughing in background]

396
00:32:56.809 --> 00:32:59.776
[both grunting]

397
00:32:59.778 --> 00:33:02.479
