I'll give you...

399
00:33:05.651 --> 00:33:09.419
Double fair market value.

400
00:33:11.956 --> 00:33:15.492
- Triple.

401
00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:17.928
- Done.

402
00:33:19.964 --> 00:33:23.600
- There are many problems
I can't solve. mr. Bohannon.

403
00:33:23.602 --> 00:33:28.672
But locating whiskey in this
sober place is not one of 'em.

404
00:33:30.208 --> 00:33:31.575
[chuckles]

405
00:33:33.678 --> 00:33:35.846
It's called valley tan.

406
00:33:35.848 --> 00:33:40.517
Made from...
Imported fire and brimstone.

407
00:33:45.790 --> 00:33:46.823
- [coughs]

408
00:33:46.825 --> 00:33:48.225
- [chuckles]

409
00:33:52.964 --> 00:33:55.866
Now. looking
for your wife and son...

410
00:33:55.868 --> 00:33:58.168
That's an ambitious undertaking.

411
00:33:58.170 --> 00:34:01.505
Especially for an ambitious man
like yourself.

412
00:34:01.507 --> 00:34:03.507
But I'm curious.
how do you begin?

413
00:34:03.509 --> 00:34:04.574
Where do you start looking?

414
00:34:04.576 --> 00:34:05.876
- I only started here.

415
00:34:05.878 --> 00:34:07.544
Now I'm heading west.

416
00:34:07.546 --> 00:34:09.980
- Mm-hmm.

417
00:34:11.582 --> 00:34:15.085
The mormon faithful...

418
00:34:15.087 --> 00:34:20.690
Are 80.000 strong.
covering almost as many miles.

419
00:34:20.692 --> 00:34:23.160
It seems to me that your plan.

420
00:34:23.162 --> 00:34:25.529
"head west."

421
00:34:25.531 --> 00:34:29.900
Is guaranteed to do only
one thing. hmm?

422
00:34:29.902 --> 00:34:34.571
Fail.

423
00:34:34.573 --> 00:34:36.039
That begs the question

424
00:34:36.041 --> 00:34:39.109
How badly do you really
want to find your family?

425
00:34:42.080 --> 00:34:47.050
- Thank you for the drink.
But I prefer rotgut.

426
00:34:47.052 --> 00:34:49.519
- If rotgut
is all that you have had.

427
00:34:49.521 --> 00:34:51.955
Rotgut is all you prefer.

428
00:34:51.957 --> 00:34:56.460
Central pacific could expand
your preferences. mr. Bohannon.

429
00:34:56.462 --> 00:34:57.761
- Uh-huh.
- Mr. Bohannon.

430
00:34:57.763 --> 00:35:02.532
There is a better way
to find your family.

431
00:35:02.534 --> 00:35:05.202
If you will indulge me.

432
00:35:08.706 --> 00:35:11.741
I plan to drive my road

433
00:35:11.743 --> 00:35:13.210
Right into the heart
of mormon country.

434
00:35:13.212 --> 00:35:17.214
From california all the way
to salt lake city.

435
00:35:17.216 --> 00:35:21.251
There is nothing that will
happen in mormon country

436
00:35:21.253 --> 00:35:24.588
That I won't know about
or can't find out about.

437
00:35:24.590 --> 00:35:27.057
Now. if you work for me.

438
00:35:27.059 --> 00:35:29.893
All of my resources
will be at your disposal.

439
00:35:33.264 --> 00:35:35.999
Your family's out there.
we'll find 'em.

440
00:35:36.001 --> 00:35:38.535
How's that sound?

441
00:35:40.338 --> 00:35:42.973
- Sounds like I'd be back
to working on the railroad.

442
00:35:42.975 --> 00:35:44.641
I've dug that ditch.

443
00:35:44.643 --> 00:35:46.643
- There's a difference
between digging a ditch

444
00:35:46.645 --> 00:35:48.812
And owning it. sir.

445
00:35:58.589 --> 00:36:00.257
Now. we will find your family.

446
00:36:00.259 --> 00:36:03.693
If that's
what you really want to do.

447
00:36:03.695 --> 00:36:06.596
But this time.
for the first time.

448
00:36:06.598 --> 00:36:08.865
You'll have something
to show them for all your work.

449
00:36:08.867 --> 00:36:12.068
More than a canvas tent
and a mud floor.

450
00:36:14.305 --> 00:36:18.074
I'm prepared to offer you
a small interest in my company.

451
00:36:20.311 --> 00:36:22.746
How does that sound?

452
00:36:39.630 --> 00:36:42.632
